data.title: Seychelles Population, 1960
data.meta_description: In 2023, population for Seychelles was 120,622 persons. Population of Seychelles increased from 57,937 persons in 1974 to 120,622 persons in 2023 growing at an average annual rate of 1.55%. Total population is based on the de facto definition of population, which counts all residents regardless of legal status or citizenship--except for refugees not permanently settled in the country of asylum, who are generally considered part of the population of their country of origin. The values shown are midyear estimates.
data.text:
What is population?

Total population is based on the de facto definition of population, which counts all residents regardless of legal status or citizenship--except for refugees not permanently settled in the country of asylum, who are generally considered part of the population of their country of origin. The values shown are midyear estimates.
